HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karin mutane 14 cikin 100 da suka kamu da cutar
Kasar Sin ta samu karuwar sabbin masu dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu a kasar.
Kimanin sabbin mutane 40,000 ne aka samu a cikin kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sabbin cututtukan an watsa su ta hanyar jima'i, wanda shine canji daga yanayin da ya gabata.
A baya, cutar HIV ta yadu da sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon ƙarin jini da ke dauke da kwayar cutar.
Amma, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An dakatar da nuna luwadi a kasar Sin tun shekara ta 1997, amma an ce nuna wariya ga 'yan luwadi ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Bincike ya nuna cewa saboda ra'ayin da aka saba da shi a kasar, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza da ke da dangantaka da maza suna yin aure da mata.
Sau da yawa kamuwa da cutar yana faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin irin wannan dangantaka.
A shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wani bangare na shirin magance matsalar.
